---

Despite the heat this was a busy month at Tokyo Indies, with a total of seven presentations. 

First up was "void LINK", a casual 3D strategy VR game inspired by Homeworld in development by [Zentrifuge Games](http://www.zentrifuge-games.eu). The presentation included a demo battle and showed off the ship constructor!

Next up was Gray Grofa, an in development MSX puzzle shooter from [TPM.CO Soft Works](http://www.tpmcosoft.com/). 

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-kfwe-uPj38
<iframe width="843" height="480" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/-kfwe-uPj38?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>


Senka presented a [YouTube channel](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mPwlStIKVQ8) about Unity Shaders and Fruit Pincher, a submission to the [Japan Game Awards](http://awards.cesa.or.jp/en/index.html).

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GL9Ks_qtodo
<iframe width="843" height="480" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/GL9Ks_qtodo?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>


[Kazushige Mori](https://twitter.com/Cz_mirror) presented
[Captulion](http://www.cz-mirror.jp/captulion/), an iOS vertical shooter where
you can capture enemy ships and make them into allies - including bosses!

!embed https://youtu.be/ljnLOl-vXHg
<iframe width="843" height="480" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ljnLOl-vXHg?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>


[Veltina](https://twitter.com/veltina_soft) presented the latest updates on the development of [Wish Dragon+](https://okauni.jimdo.com/games/wishdragonplus/). He also showed off his game jam game [Yokoi-san Warp](https://veltina.itch.io/yokoi-san) and [Extrival](https://okauni.jimdo.com/games/extrival/), an in-development fighting game.

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b200WiM15LM
<iframe width="843" height="480" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/b200WiM15LM?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>


[Nimu](https://twitter.com/ni26mu) presented [Darkness Sweeper](https://twitter.com/ni26mu/status/879566313793896449), a roguelike without traditional movement, as well as his next project, Darkness Duel.

!img darknesssweeper.jpg Explore by tapping on the dark squares and find the ladder to go to the next floor!

Finally [Yoshi](https://twitter.com/yoshi84863388) of [Studio Muma](http://muma.jp/) presented the in-development PC game Yume Monogatari ("Dream Story"). Explore a mysterious world full of strange characters.

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SDv_j45vpeU
<iframe width="843" height="480" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/SDv_j45vpeU?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>


That was it for this month, catch you next time! ðŸŽ®
